{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"lofty-beech-twang","description":"## Summary\nThe OPERATIONAL + high-risk tail of the convergence rollout, carved out of soar-quill-flare (7d23) so that ticket can close on its landed code deliverable. This work is owned by the operator of the deployed `.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml` (runs `rebar reconcile --mode live` every 20 min from main); it CANNOT run in an agent session because it needs live production Jira and ~3.5h+ of real 20-min-apart passes.\n\n## What is already landed (in 7d23, on main)\n- Phase-1 baseline dual-write SHADOW (`baseline_shadow.py`) behind `reconciler.baseline_dual_write`, with per-pass `baseline_shadow_check` logging + `baseline_shadow_divergence` alert.\n- Circuit breaker (`check_blast_radius`, default 0.10) enforced before the first acting mutation of the level-triggered walk.\n- Rollback controls + procedure documented in `docs/jira-sync-setup.md`.\n\n## Remaining CODE (safe, agent-doable but deliberately deferred behind live gate)\n- Phase-3 consumer swap: re-point `outbound_fields._local_matches_prev` (and its `outbound_differ` caller) from prev_snapshot to `BindingStore.get_baseline`, behind a flag. PRESERVE byte-for-byte: absent-baseline->local-wins degrade; corrupt-store fail-closed pass abort; direction arbitration (ADR 0026 #1-#3). prev_snapshot retained for L3 single-pass suppression.\n- RED-first direction-preservation property test running against the SWAPPED consumer.\n- decision_census emitted every pass in EVERY mode + classifier-vs-legacy divergence alerting in shadow (Phase-2 breadth).\n\n## Remaining OPERATIONAL (needs live prod Jira + deployed workflow)\n- >= 10 consecutive clean live shadow passes (`baseline_shadow_check` divergent==0), ~3.5h wall clock, BEFORE flipping the Phase-3 consumer flag.\n- Capped live heal under bootstrap-strict (MODE_CAPS=10) of the 7 known drift instances: REB-464/456/465/466/457 (archived->Done), f8b5-2f30->REB-530 (GC-after-grace), REB-532 (adopt); then assert the NEXT pass census reports 0 acting decisions (fixed point on live data); then return to live.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Phase-3 consumer-swap code merged behind a flag with the direction-preservation property test against the swapped consumer; corrupt-baseline fail-closed abort preserved; prev_snapshot retained for L3.\n- [ ] decision_census emitted every pass in every mode; classifier-vs-legacy divergence logged + alerting in shadow.\n- [ ] >= 10 consecutive clean live shadow passes recorded (cite pass ids) before the consumer flag is flipped.\n- [ ] The 7 known drift instances healed under bootstrap-strict caps; next-pass census = 0 acting decisions; census log excerpts attached.\n- [ ] Consumer flag flipped in production only after the two gates above; rollback (pin workflow mode to dry-run) rehearsed.","id":"a118-fa8e-547a-49ba","parent_id":"3006-e198-13db-4e1f","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Convergence rollout tail: Phase-3 consumer swap flip + live shadow-pass validation + capped live heal"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783138514216595001,"uuid":"c28bfea4-9eef-4504-8403-68b2858c0454"}